description:
Robert Fisk is one of the most respected writers in journalism today. He has lived in the Middle East for over 30 years and writes for The Independent. 

In this talk, introduced by Noam Chomsky, he discusses his first hand experiences in Iraq, the Armenian genocide in Turkey and problems with contemporary journalism in the UK and US.

He is the author of The Great War for Civilization. A weighty and hard hitting tome that documents problems in the Middle East and their historical roots.



